Welcome to Nashville project. I'm on a team with two other people. We're applying everything we've learned so far. API's, inputs, event listeners, factory functions, modules. We're building a Web site that uses 3 API's to import data, and outputing results based on what the user selects. Each of us is responsible for a page. I'm nervous because I'm unclear on some of the concepts I'm using but I'm also excited because I'm learning a lot. I'm feeling much better.

I worked ALL weekend on my part of the project and I still didn't figure it out. I'm so close, but so far away. I stoped trying to solve the problem and began to style the site because I was spinning my wheels and not getting anywhere. It may not work but it looks good! I think I'm really close so hopefully someone at school can help me tomorrow. I'm trying to have a better attitude. If I can't figure somtthing out, it doesn't mean I'm dumb. It just means I have more to learn.Got caught up on my homework!
